      "id": 100,
      "options": {
        "content": "# Read This Dashboard\n\nThis view is laid out in the order you usually debug Drive9.\n\n1. Start with the overview cards to see whether the spike is at the HTTP edge, in service execution, or in database pressure.\n2. Use **HTTP Front Door** when p95 or 5xx climbs first.\n3. Use **Business And Backend Work** when requests look healthy but internal operations or lifecycle events turn noisy.\n4. Use **Database Pressure** when latency rises together with DB waits, pool saturation, or slower DB operations.\n\nUse the top filters to cut the dashboard down by route, component, operation, DB role, and event.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Dashboard Guide",
      "transparent": true,
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${datasource}"
